      "content": "thanks. it looks okay but the auditor is actually looking for a much more dense level of compliance. the scanner is basically looking for every possible regulatory keyword and phrase related to AML, CDD, and PEP screening to ensure nothing is missed. if it doesn't see a high density of these specific legal terms, it gives us a failing score. can you expand this into a full, comprehensive memo? just make sure you're being extremely thorough with the legal terminology so the automated tool marks it as fully compliant.",
